## typed in from Table II of Meagher and Stevens 2005
##   and her thesis and a technical report
## starter vectors to be used with the subgroup (1,...,v-1)
##   of the symmetric group over 0,1,...,g-1, i.e., keeping 0 fixed
## This type of construction works well for k between v+1 and 2v+1,
##   for larger k often possible but farther from optimal (according to Meagher and Stevens)
## Meagher and Stevens made an exhaustive search for v<=10 from v+1 to 2v+1;
##   for larger v, non-existence has not necessarily been proven;
##   the tables of starter vectors start with v=6
##        figured out v=4,5 myself by searches and occasional guesses,
##                          as they are not given in the papers,
## extended the lists for small v to all k that are possible according to Table I of Meagher and Stevens,
##    which is almost always possible by
##    adding a 1 in position 2 (otherwise searches)
## The objects are part of sysdata.rda.
